commit.message:
Correctly use C_GetSlotList() git PKCS#11 2.40

Use a double call to C_GetSlotList() so that the module list is
correctly initialized.

Fix "trouble using PyKCS11 with libbeidpkcs11 #73"
https://github.com/LudovicRousseau/PyKCS11/issues/73

test_wrap: fix UT now that isBool is fixed

PyKCS11.CKA_EXTRACTABLE attribute is a boolean now.

CK_ATTRIBUTE_SMART::IsBool(): 3 new booleans

CKA_ALWAYS_AUTHENTICATE, CKA_EXTRACTABLE & CKA_WRAP_WITH_TRUSTED are
boolean attributes.

IsBool() (C code) is now in sync with isBool() (Python code)

test_asymetric.py: use a correct size for RSA_PSS_Mechanism.sLen

All PSS mechanisms require to provide the PSS parameters in appropriate
C_XXXInit() APIs. The PKCS#11 recommends to use salt length equal to
appropriate hash length.

For SHA1: salt length = 20 bytes
For SHA256: salt length = 32 bytes

Use hex in CKM_VENDOR_DEFINED_...

Use CKM_VENDOR_DEFINED_0x45 instdead of CKM_VENDOR_DEFINED_45 to
indicates the value is in hex.

The real value returned by the PKCS#11 lib is
CKM_VENDOR_DEFINED + 0x45 = 0x80000045

Fix name for VENDOR_DEFINED mechanisms

The correct name is CKM_VENDOR_DEFINED_6001 instead of CKR_VENDOR_DEFINED_6001
since it is a mechanism.

MANIFEST: fix build on Windows from pip

Add missing resource.h
Also add dev-requirements.txt, docs/* and COPYING

Thanks to Slav Agafs for the bug report

MANIFEST: fix build on Windows from pip

Add missing pykcs11.rc

Thanks to Slav Agafs for the bug report
test_ckbytelist: check the .text field of the exception

ckbytelist(): store a string in the .text of an exception

If the format is unknown then the .text field of the generated exception
now contains a string representation of the type instead of the type
itself.

This change does not solve a real bug but I think an .text field should
be a Python string.
test_pin: check the exception string representation

test_load: unit test for PyKCS11.PyKCS11Lib().load()

Test the high level function.
test_LowLevel.py: test new values for CPKCS11Lib.Load()
